---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../styles/applying.css';

const jsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "CollectionPage",
  "name": "Applying in Public",
  "url": "https://amit.so/applying",
  "description": "A real-time video series in which Amit Arora documents his job search — AI-powered resume tailoring, outbound experiments, and what he's learning along the way.",
  "isPartOf": {
    "@type": "WebSite",
    "name": "Amit Arora",
    "url": "https://amit.so"
  },
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Amit Arora",
    "url": "https://amit.so"
  }
});
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Applying in Public | Amit Arora"
  description="Applying in Public — Amit Arora documents his job search in real time, sharing the AI-powered toolkit, outbound experiments, and lessons from each episode."
  canonical="https://amit.so/applying"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <div class="grain"></div>

  <nav>
    <a href="/" class="nav-brand">amit.so</a>
    <a href="/" class="nav-back">&larr; Back to Portfolio</a>
  </nav>

  <main>
    <div class="series-badge fade-up">Live series</div>

    <h1 class="fade-up">Applying in Public</h1>

    <p class="series-intro fade-up">
      No curated highlight reel. No &ldquo;excited to announce&rdquo; post after the fact. This is the real-time, unfiltered documentation of a job search &mdash; the strategy, the tools, the rejections, and the wins. Follow along as I look for my next Revenue Operations role at a Series A/B startup, powered by an AI-first workflow.
    </p>

    <div class="episode-card fade-up">
      <div class="episode-label">Episode 1 &mdash; Day 1</div>
      <div class="episode-title">Laid Off on a Friday. Documenting Everything This Time.</div>
      <div class="video-wrap">
        <iframe src="https://player.mediadelivery.net/embed/637647/351af434-18aa-4177-a139-7a20ef1830bc?autoplay=false&loop=false&muted=false&preload=true&responsive=true" loading="lazy" allow="accelerometer;gyroscope;autoplay;encrypted-media;picture-in-picture;" allowfullscreen="true"></iframe>
      </div>
      <div class="episode-gist">
        <p>After being laid off, I decided to do something different this time &mdash; <strong>document the entire job search publicly</strong>. Drawing on lessons from a 2024 layoff, I&rsquo;m building a modern, AI-powered job search toolkit: <strong>LinkedIn</strong> for sourcing roles, <strong>HubSpot</strong> for tracking applications as a pipeline, <strong>Perplexity</strong> for company research, <strong>Claude</strong> for tailoring resumes, and <strong>OpenClaw</strong> for automating CRM updates. The target: a Revenue Operations leadership role at a Series A/B startup, backed by 10+ years across Slalom, DHI Group, and webAI.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tools-used">
        <span class="tool-tag">LinkedIn</span>
        <span class="tool-tag">HubSpot</span>
        <span class="tool-tag">Perplexity</span>
        <span class="tool-tag">Claude</span>
        <span class="tool-tag">OpenClaw</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="episode-card fade-up">
      <div class="episode-label">Episode 2 &mdash; Day 2</div>
      <div class="episode-title">AI-Tailored Resumes: From Job Post to Submission in Minutes</div>
      <div class="video-wrap">
        <iframe src="https://player.mediadelivery.net/embed/637647/265f1484-d745-481c-bcbf-6f7b19b842ad?autoplay=false&loop=false&muted=false&preload=true&responsive=true" loading="lazy" allow="accelerometer;gyroscope;autoplay;encrypted-media;picture-in-picture;" allowfullscreen="true"></iframe>
      </div>
      <div class="episode-gist">
        <p>Day 2 of applying in public. I walk through my full AI-assisted application workflow: browsing <strong>LinkedIn</strong> for RevOps roles at Series A/B startups, filtering out companies that are too large, and landing on a <strong>GTM Engineer role at Stedi</strong>. From there, I use a <strong>custom Claude skill</strong> to analyze the job description against my resume &mdash; identifying gaps, surfacing strong matches, and automatically generating a tailored resume. The final step: exporting to <strong>Google Docs</strong> for a quick review before hitting submit.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tools-used">
        <span class="tool-tag">LinkedIn</span>
        <span class="tool-tag">Claude</span>
        <span class="tool-tag">Google Docs</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cta-section fade-up">
      <p class="cta-heading">Hiring? Or want to follow the journey?</p>
      <p class="cta-body">If your team needs a RevOps or GTM Engineer hire, the fastest path is a 15-minute conversation. If you&rsquo;re just here to follow the series, LinkedIn is where new episodes drop first.</p>
      <div class="cta-actions">
        <a href="/interview" class="cta-btn cta-btn-primary">Book a Call &rarr;</a>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/amit-arora17/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cta-btn cta-btn-secondary">Follow on LinkedIn &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>
    &copy; 2026 Amit Arora &middot; <a href="/">amit.so</a> &middot; <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a> &middot; <a href="#" onclick="event.preventDefault(); window.showCookiePreferences && window.showCookiePreferences();">Cookies</a>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
